text: Hey everyone, It's a pleasure to join the group.  My name is Lynn Renoll (Jr).  I live in Brookhaven, GA.  I am actually a graduate of OMSCS (class of '17).   I am not sure if I am the only OMSCS alumni here yet.  David Joyner asked if I wanted to be included so I said why not.  :slightly_smiling_face:  It is amazing how time flies by.  It seems like just yesterday that I was in class.  It can be quite challenging at times, but I found it oddly quite a lot of fun.  In my spare time I like to run/jog and listen to music.  Been reading some books recently as well.  As a side note, at one time there was a local meetup group here in town that would have a get together every few months or so but I don't think that they meet anymore (I could be wrong).  Hope to see some of you around sometime.

text:
Hi everyone!  I'm in Sandy Springs, graduated in FA18 from OMSCS specializing in ML.  I worked as a Research Scientist at GT as well in the DILab, was a TA for SP22 for ML, and taught a seminar in SU22 on ML/DS OSS tools.  Also just got accepted into the OMS Cybersecurity program for SP23, so just can't stay away.  :crazy_grin:

Currently working at IBM Security as a backend threat intel engineer.
